==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cutback
<hw>cutback</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a reduction in quantity
or rate; a reduction in the amount of an activity or the funding for an
activity; <as>as, <ex>cutbacks</ex> in government research funding
increased unemployment among scientists; the recession caused a
<ex>cutback</ex> in auto production</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a return to an earlier scene or story line in a
novel, movie, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Sports)</fld> <def>a sudden switching of directions
of a running football player, a surfboarder, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cutch</ent>⟦br⟧
